<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="556" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[389,512,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Hovops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[389,512,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">H. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the shape of the well developed RTA, with a sigmoid dorsal branch, not spiral shaped, an embolus shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[762,901,188,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Hovops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modestus">
<emphasis box="[762,901,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">H. modestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a large triangular projection on the outer edge, and by the shape and structure of the conductor (figs 
<number box="[813,826,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="8.0">8</number>
b–c, 
<bibRefCitation author="Corronca" box="[881,1294,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" refString="Corronca, J. A. &amp; Rodriguez Artigas, S. M. (2011) New species of the Madagascan genus Hovops Benoit, 1968 (Araneae: Selenopidae), with a description of the H. madagascariensis male and an identification key. African Invertebrates, 52, 295 - 310. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 052.0206" type="journal article" year="2011">
Corronca &amp; Rodriguez Artigas 
<number box="[1234,1294,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,272,260,284]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Hovops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">H. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from others of the genus by the large middle field occupying nearly the entire epigyne surface; the cordiform lateral lobes near posterior end, and the shape of the copulatory ducts and spermathecae (figs 
<number box="[151,164,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="8.0">8</number>
d–e, 
<bibRefCitation author="Corronca" box="[219,632,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" refString="Corronca, J. A. &amp; Rodriguez Artigas, S. M. (2011) New species of the Madagascan genus Hovops Benoit, 1968 (Araneae: Selenopidae), with a description of the H. madagascariensis male and an identification key. African Invertebrates, 52, 295 - 310. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 052.0206" type="journal article" year="2011">
Corronca &amp; Rodriguez Artigas 
<number box="[572,632,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556">Note</emphasis>
: The female was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[623,783,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" refString="Simon, E. (1887) Especes et genres nouveaux de la famille des Sparassidae. Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France, 12, 466 - 474." type="journal article" year="1887">
Simon (
<number box="[715,775,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and the same author in 
<number box="[1075,1131,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="1897.0">1897</number>
described the male of the species and included a drawing of the RTA of the male palp. 
<bibRefCitation box="[869,1327,404,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" refString="Corronca, J. A. &amp; Rodriguez Artigas, S. M. (2011) New species of the Madagascan genus Hovops Benoit, 1968 (Araneae: Selenopidae), with a description of the H. madagascariensis male and an identification key. African Invertebrates, 52, 295 - 310. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 052.0206" type="journal article">
Corronca and Rodriguez Artigas (
<number box="[1261,1319,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="556" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
provided photographs of the female habitus and female and male genitalia.
</paragraph>
